colubrisPublicAccessMIB.name: colubrisPublicAccessMIB
colubrisPublicAccessMIB.contactinfo: Colubris Networks Postal: 200 West Street Ste 300 Waltham, Massachusetts 02451-1121 UNITED STATES Phone: +1 781 684 0001 Fax: +1 781 684 0009 E-mail: cn-snmp@colubris.com

publicAccessStatus.name: publicAccessStatus
publicAccessStatus.description: Identifies the current status of the authentication system.

publicAccessStatusChangedCause.name: publicAccessStatusChangedCause
publicAccessStatusChangedCause.description: Identifies the last cause of a status change. Mostly used by the publicAccessStatusChanged trap.

publicAccessDeviceUserName.name: publicAccessDeviceUserName
publicAccessDeviceUserName.description: Specifies the username that the device uses when authenticating itself to a RADIUS server.

publicAccessDeviceUserPassword.name: publicAccessDeviceUserPassword
publicAccessDeviceUserPassword.description: Specifies the password the device uses when authenticating to a RADIUS server. For security reasons, this should be set only if SNMP traffic is sent through a VPN tunnel. Reading this attribute will return an empty string.

publicAccessDeviceSessionTimeoutAdminSta.name: publicAccessDeviceSessionTimeoutAdminStatus
publicAccessDeviceSessionTimeoutAdminSta.description: Specifies the interval of time between two consecutive authentication attempts in minutes. At each successful authentication the device configuration is refreshed. This is not the time between RADIUS Access Request when an authentication is proceeding without answers. For that element, see the RADIUS Profile definition.

publicAccessDeviceSessionTimeoutOperStat.name: publicAccessDeviceSessionTimeoutOperStatus
publicAccessDeviceSessionTimeoutOperStat.description: Identifies the interval of time between two consecutive authentication attempts in seconds. At each successful authentication the device configuration is refreshed. This is not the time between RADIUS Access Request when an authentication is proceeding without answers. For that element, see the RADIUS Profile definition.

publicAccessDeviceConfigMode.name: publicAccessDeviceConfigMode
publicAccessDeviceConfigMode.description: Identifies how configuration of the device is performed. This can be via locally configured settings on the device, or retrieved from a AAA server. If both options are enabled, the settings retrieved from the AAA server overwrite the local configuration settings.

publicAccessDeviceAuthenProfileIndex.name: publicAccessDeviceAuthenProfileIndex
publicAccessDeviceAuthenProfileIndex.description: Identifies the AAA server profile to use to authenticate the device. This attribute only applies when publicAccessDeviceConfigMode is set to 'profile' or 'localAndProfile'. When the special value zero is specified, no AAA server profile is selected.

publicAccessDeviceAccountingEnabled.name: publicAccessDeviceAccountingEnabled
publicAccessDeviceAccountingEnabled.description: Identifies if accounting information is generated by the device and sent to the AAA server. The device generate RADIUS accounting of type ON and OFF. This also covers accounting of all access-lists independently of where they are used. For accounting, the following status types are generated: START, INTERIM-UPDATE, and STOP. Accounting information is generated only if a valid AAA server profile is configured in the publicAccessDeviceAccountingProfileIndex attribute.

publicAccessDeviceAccountingProfileIndex.name: publicAccessDeviceAccountingProfileIndex
publicAccessDeviceAccountingProfileIndex.description: Identifies the AAA server profile to use for device accounting. This attribute only applies when publicAccessDeviceAccountingEnabled is set to 'enable'. When the special value zero is specified, the value set inside publicAccessDeviceAuthenProfileIndex is used instead.

publicAccessDeviceForceReconfiguration.name: publicAccessDeviceForceReconfiguration
publicAccessDeviceForceReconfiguration.description: Specify forceReconfiguration(1) to force the device to re-read the local configuration file or re-issue an authentication request to the AAA server, or both based on the value of the publicAccessDeviceConfigMode attribute. Reading this object always returns 'idle'. Re-issuing an authentication only applies if a valid AAA server profile is specified in publicAccessDeviceAuthenProfileIndex.

publicAccessUsersMaxCount.name: publicAccessUsersMaxCount
publicAccessUsersMaxCount.description: Indicates the maximum number of concurrent authenticated users.

publicAccessUsersCount.name: publicAccessUsersCount
publicAccessUsersCount.description: Indicates the number of currently authenticated users.

publicAccessUsersThreshold.name: publicAccessUsersThreshold
publicAccessUsersThreshold.description: Specifies the trigger value for sending the publicAccessUsersThresholdTrap. When the number of users logged into the public access interface is equal to or exceeds this threshold value, a publicAccessUsersThresholdTrap is sent. The threshold value cannot exceed publicAccessUsersMaxCount or an error is returned. Set this to zero to disable sending of the publicAccessUsersThresholdTrap.

publicAccessUsersSessionTrapEnabled.name: publicAccessUsersSessionTrapEnabled
publicAccessUsersSessionTrapEnabled.description: When set to enable, the publicAccessUsersSessionStart and publicAccessUsersSessionStop traps are generated when a user session begins or ends.

publicAccessUsersConfigTable.name: publicAccessUsersConfigTable
publicAccessUsersConfigTable.description: Provides information on the user's authentication method. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

publicAccessUsersConfigIndex.name: publicAccessUsersConfigIndex
publicAccessUsersConfigIndex.description: Index of a user profile in the publicAccessUsersConfigTable.

publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenType.name: publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenType
publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenType.description: Indicates the mechanism used to authenticate users.

publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenMode.name: publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenMode
publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenMode.description: Specifies how the user authentication is performed. It can be done with the local user list or via a AAA server profile. If both are enabled, the local user list is checked first.

publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenProfileInde.name: publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenProfileIndex
publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenProfileInde.description: Specifies the AAA profile to use for user authentication when publicAccessUsersAuthenMode is set to 'profile' or 'localAndProfile'.

publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenTimeout.name: publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenTimeout
publicAccessUsersConfigAuthenTimeout.description: Logins are refused if the AAA server does not respond within this time period. Only applies when coVirtualApUserAccessAuthenMode is set to 'profile' or 'localAndProfile' and when the users are authenticated via 'HTML' or 'MAC' authentication.

publicAccessUsersConfigAccountingEnabled.name: publicAccessUsersConfigAccountingEnabled
publicAccessUsersConfigAccountingEnabled.description: Indicates if accounting information is generated by the device and sent to the AAA server for public access users. Accounting information is generated only if a valid AAA server profile is configured for publicAccessUsersAccountingProfileIndex.

publicAccessUsersConfigAccountingProfile.name: publicAccessUsersConfigAccountingProfileIndex
publicAccessUsersConfigAccountingProfile.description: Identifies the AAA profile to send accounting to for public access users. When zero is specified, the value set inside publicAccessDeviceAuthenProfileIndex is used instead.

publicAccessUsersConfigInterfaceIndex.name: publicAccessUsersConfigInterfaceIndex
publicAccessUsersConfigInterfaceIndex.description: Indicates the local interface on which these configuration parameters apply. This attribute is used with the publicAccessUsersConfigVirtualApProfileIndex to uniquely identify an entry in Virtual AP indexed tables.

publicAccessUsersConfigVirtualApProfileI.name: publicAccessUsersConfigVirtualApProfileIndex
publicAccessUsersConfigVirtualApProfileI.description: Indicates a user's VAP profile currently associated with these configuration parameters. This attribute is used with the publicAccessUsersConfigInterfaceIndex to uniquely identify an entry in Virtual AP indexed tables.

publicAccessUserTable.name: publicAccessUserTable
publicAccessUserTable.description: A table containing specific information for users authenticated by the authentication system. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

publicAccessUserEntry.name: publicAccessUserEntry
publicAccessUserEntry.description: Information about a particular user that has been authenticated by the authentication system. publicAccessUserIndex - Uniquely identifies a user in the table.

publicAccessUserIndex.name: publicAccessUserIndex
publicAccessUserIndex.description: Index of a user in the publicAccessUserTable.

publicAccessUserAuthenType.name: publicAccessUserAuthenType
publicAccessUserAuthenType.description: Indicates the mechanism used to authenticate the user.

publicAccessUserAuthenMode.name: publicAccessUserAuthenMode
publicAccessUserAuthenMode.description: Specifies how user authentication is performed. It can be done using a local user list defined on the device or AAA server profile. If both modes are active the local user list is checked first.

publicAccessUserState.name: publicAccessUserState
publicAccessUserState.description: Indicates the current state of the user.

publicAccessUserSessionStartTime.name: publicAccessUserSessionStartTime
publicAccessUserSessionStartTime.description: Indicates when this user session was started.

publicAccessUserSessionDuration.name: publicAccessUserSessionDuration
publicAccessUserSessionDuration.description: Indicates how long the user's session has been active. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserIdleTime.name: publicAccessUserIdleTime
publicAccessUserIdleTime.description: Indicates for how long the user's session has been idle. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserBytesSent.name: publicAccessUserBytesSent
publicAccessUserBytesSent.description: Indicates the total number of bytes sent by the user. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserBytesReceived.name: publicAccessUserBytesReceived
publicAccessUserBytesReceived.description: Indicates the total number of bytes received by the user. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserPacketsSent.name: publicAccessUserPacketsSent
publicAccessUserPacketsSent.description: Indicates the total number of IP packets sent by the user. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserPacketsReceived.name: publicAccessUserPacketsReceived
publicAccessUserPacketsReceived.description: Indicates the total number of IP packets received by the user. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserForceDisconnection.name: publicAccessUserForceDisconnection
publicAccessUserForceDisconnection.description: Setting this attribute to 'adminReset' disconnects the user with a cause of ADMIN_RESET. Reading this variable always return 'idle'.

publicAccessUserApMacAddress.name: publicAccessUserApMacAddress
publicAccessUserApMacAddress.description: Indicates the user's Access Point MAC Address when Location- Aware is enabled or the Access Controller MAC Address.

publicAccessUserGroupName.name: publicAccessUserGroupName
publicAccessUserGroupName.description: Indicates the user's Access Point Group Name (ONLY when Location-aware is enabled and properly configured). If this information is not available, a zero-Length string is returned.

publicAccessUserSSID.name: publicAccessUserSSID
publicAccessUserSSID.description: Indicates the user's Access Point SSID (ONLY when Location-aware is enabled and properly configured). If this information is not available, a zero-Length string is returned.

publicAccessUserVLAN.name: publicAccessUserVLAN
publicAccessUserVLAN.description: Specifies the VLAN currently assigned to the user.

publicAccessUserApRadioIndex.name: publicAccessUserApRadioIndex
publicAccessUserApRadioIndex.description: Indicates the radio to which this user is associated. The index 0 is reserved when location aware is not enabled or not properly configured. It means that the system could not determine on which interface the user is connected. Please note that this information is not related to the standard SNMP interface table. It is a proprietary index information on the Radios in Colubris devices.

publicAccessUserConfigIndex.name: publicAccessUserConfigIndex
publicAccessUserConfigIndex.description: Indicates the configuration profile in the publicAccessUsersConfigTable currently associated with this user. When location aware is not enabled or not properly configured, the first SSID of the first radio interface is used as the default configuration profile.

publicAccessUserConnectedInterface.name: publicAccessUserConnectedInterface
publicAccessUserConnectedInterface.description: Indicates the device's logical public interface to which the user is connected. This will always be a string containing 'br0'.

publicAccessUserBytesSentDropped.name: publicAccessUserBytesSentDropped
publicAccessUserBytesSentDropped.description: Indicates the total number of bytes sent by the user and dropped due to rate limitation. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserBytesReceivedDropped.name: publicAccessUserBytesReceivedDropped
publicAccessUserBytesReceivedDropped.description: Indicates the total number of bytes received for the user and dropped due to rate limitation. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserPacketsSentDropped.name: publicAccessUserPacketsSentDropped
publicAccessUserPacketsSentDropped.description: Indicates the total number of packets sent by the user and dropped due to rate limitation. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserPacketsReceivedDropped.name: publicAccessUserPacketsReceivedDropped
publicAccessUserPacketsReceivedDropped.description: Indicates the total number of packets received for the user and dropped due to rate limitation. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

publicAccessUserRateLimitationEnabled.name: publicAccessUserRateLimitationEnabled
publicAccessUserRateLimitationEnabled.description: Specifies if rate limitation is enabled for the user.

publicAccessUserMaxTransmitRate.name: publicAccessUserMaxTransmitRate
publicAccessUserMaxTransmitRate.description: Specifies the maximum transmit rate for the user.

publicAccessUserMaxReceiveRate.name: publicAccessUserMaxReceiveRate
publicAccessUserMaxReceiveRate.description: Specifies the maximum receive rate for the user.

publicAccessUserBandwidthControlLevel.name: publicAccessUserBandwidthControlLevel
publicAccessUserBandwidthControlLevel.description: Specifies the user's bandwidth control level.

publicAccessUserNASPort.name: publicAccessUserNASPort
publicAccessUserNASPort.description: Specifies the NAS-Port value assigned to the user.

publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrapEnabled.name: publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrapEnabled
publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrapEnabled.description: When set to enable, the publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrap is generated.

publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrapInterval.name: publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrapInterval
publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrapInterval.description: Interval between publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrap traps. Setting this to 0 will disable periodic sending of these traps.

publicAccessNASPortCount.name: publicAccessNASPortCount
publicAccessNASPortCount.description: Indicates the number of NAS-Port supported.

publicAccessNASPortTable.name: publicAccessNASPortTable
publicAccessNASPortTable.description: A table containing specific information for NAS-Port by the Access Controller. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

publicAccessNASPortEntry.name: publicAccessNASPortEntry
publicAccessNASPortEntry.description: Information about a particular NAS-Port by Access Controller. publicAccessNASPortIndex - Uniquely identifies a NAS-Port in the table.

publicAccessNASPortIndex.name: publicAccessNASPortIndex
publicAccessNASPortIndex.description: Index of a NAS-Port in the publicAccessNASPortTable.

publicAccessNASPortUserName.name: publicAccessNASPortUserName
publicAccessNASPortUserName.description: Indicates the user's name currently authenticated by the Access Controller on this NAS-Port.

publicAccessStatusChangedTrap.name: publicAccessStatusChangedTrap
publicAccessStatusChangedTrap.description: This notification is sent whenever the authentication system status changes (up or down).

publicAccessUsersThresholdTrap.name: publicAccessUsersThresholdTrap
publicAccessUsersThresholdTrap.description: This notification is sent whenever publicAccessUsersThreshold is exceeded.

publicAccessUsersSessionStartTrap.name: publicAccessUsersSessionStartTrap
publicAccessUsersSessionStartTrap.description: When a user successfully authenticate a trap is generated if the publicAccessUsersSessionTrapEnabled is set to True.

publicAccessUsersSessionStopTrap.name: publicAccessUsersSessionStopTrap
publicAccessUsersSessionStopTrap.description: When a user terminates their session a trap is generated if the publicAccessUsersSessionTrapEnabled is set to True.

publicAccessUsersSessionFailTrap.name: publicAccessUsersSessionFailTrap
publicAccessUsersSessionFailTrap.description: When a user authentication fails a trap is generated if the publicAccessUsersSessionTrapEnabled is set to True.

publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrap.name: publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrap
publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrap.description: This is sent when a user is authenticated or periodically (see publicAccessUSersLoggedInTrapInterval) if the publicAccessUsersLoggedInTrapEnabled is set to True.

colubrisPublicAccessMIBCompliance.name: colubrisPublicAccessMIBCompliance
colubrisPublicAccessMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Colubris Public Access MIB.

colubrisPublicAccessMIBGroup.name: colubrisPublicAccessMIBGroup
colubrisPublicAccessMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing control over the Public Access MIB.

colubrisPublicAccessUserMIBGroup.name: colubrisPublicAccessUserMIBGroup
colubrisPublicAccessUserMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the Public Access MIB capability.

colubrisPublicAccessUserConfigMIBGroup.name: colubrisPublicAccessUserConfigMIBGroup
colubrisPublicAccessUserConfigMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the Public Access user configuration capability.

colubrisPublicAccessNASPortsMIBGroup.name: colubrisPublicAccessNASPortsMIBGroup
colubrisPublicAccessNASPortsMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the Public Access NAS Port MIB capability.
